{{DISPLAYTITLE:<center><span style="background:linear-gradient(90deg,#d4af37,#f2d675,#c89b3c); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent; text-shadow: canary 6px 8.0px 12px; font-family:libre baskerville;"><big>'''Level 228: Alan's Psychedelic Breakfast'''</big></span>}}{{Class 3|hexagon=3|font=Libre Baskerville|color-h=gold|color-s=#E6C55A|color-l=#E6C55A}}

<span style="font-family:Georgia">'''Level 228''', also known as '''"Alan's Psychedelic Breakfast",''' is the 229<sup>th</sup> discovered level of the Backrooms.</span>  
{{Blurimage|file=House228.png|hovertext=Alan's House|caption=An image of '''Level 228''' upon entering.|bg-align=Right|align=Right|}}

== <span style="color:#D4AF37;"><span style="font-family:Georgia">Description </span> </span> ==
<span style="font-family:Georgia">'''Level 228''' is a three-story, isolated house located in the middle of an endless grassy field. The house's architecture is perceptually unstable: the external size is significantly smaller than the internal volume. The space within is sterile, white, and glassy. Objects within the house exhibit spatial instability, changing in size or position when not observed. Despite these anomalies, the house's structure remains functionally stable and repeatable. At this level, no identifiable energy source has been recorded.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">A quiet piano composition plays throughout the level. The sound has no visible source, but observations show it directly influences the behavior of the wanderers, triggering hunger and a desire to eat.</span>  

<span style="font-family:Georgia">[[Phenomenon 15]] is observed at this level, as a result of which, upon entering, the level creates a separate space for each one. {{Blurimage|file=Night228.png|hovertext=Night|caption=Nighttime.|bg-align=Right|align=Right}}The level's time cycle is fixed at approximately two hours, after which there is an abrupt transition between day and night.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Level 228's planet lacks a star; a momentary darkening of the sky indicates the state change. At night, the level's activity changes abruptly: the musical accompaniment ceases, and the external environment becomes deadly due to extremely low temperatures.</span>

<span style="font-family:Georgia">[[M.E.G.]] researchers have noted a potential correlation between Level 228 and anomalous cognitive activity associated with [[Entity 96]], known as "Alan". Structural and environmental changes occur concurrently with these fluctuations, though the nature of this relationship remains unknown.</span>  

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Prolonged stay on the level causes gradual amnesia, especially regarding taste and familiar food sensations. Temporary memory loss is also observed, partially restored after leaving the level.</span>  

<span style="font-family:Georgia">With repeated visits of this level, a gradual degradation of perception is observed:</span>  

* <span style="font-family:Georgia">The house becomes less stable</span>  
* <span style="font-family:Georgia">Food loses its taste</span>  
* <span style="font-family:Georgia">Anxiety increases</span>  
* <span style="font-family:Georgia">The feeling of being watched increases</span>  
* <span style="font-family:Georgia">Alan’s behavior toward individuals shows signs of deterioration over time.</span>  
=== <span style="color:#D4AF37;"><span style="font-family:Georgia">Rooms</span></span> ===
<span style="font-family:Georgia">There are only 7 rooms on this level: The Kitchen, The Hall, Timeout Bath, The Staircase, The Bedroom, and The Attic.</span>
<tabber>
|-|The Bedroom=
{{Blurimage|file=Bedroom228.png|hovertext=Rise and shine|caption=<span style="font-family:Georgia">An image of The Bedroom.</span>|bg-align=Right|align=Right}}
<span style="font-family:Georgia">'''The Bedroom''' is the room in the house where individuals who enter this level awaken. The room is a large space with a bed and a lamp in the middle. This zone is the exit from the level.</span>  
|-| The Kitchen=
{{Blurimage|file=TheKitchen228.png|hovertext=The Kitchen|caption=<span style="font-family:Georgia">An image of The Kitchen</span>|bg-align=Right|align=Right}}
<span style="font-family:Georgia">'''The Kitchen''' is the central area of Level 228 and the most frequently occupied space by [[Entity 96]]. The room is sterile and consistently contains prepared food and drink at the table.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Food manifests at regular intervals through an unknown autonomous process. The mechanism behind its production remains unobserved, and no definitive source has been identified.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Alan is frequently observed in The Kitchen during these occurrences, though no interaction with the food generation process has been confirmed.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Attempts to interrupt the food cycle have resulted in inconsistent environmental responses, including increased hunger sensations and spatial disorientation, with no observed effect on the generation process itself.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">The Kitchen appears to function independently of any observable entity or mechanical system.</span>
|-| The Attic=
{{Blurimage|file=Attic228.png|hovertext=The Attic|caption=<span style="font-family:Georgia">An image of pipe leading to The Attic.</span>|bg-align=Right|align=Right}}
<span style="font-family:Georgia">A smooth pipe leads to '''The Attic''' on Level 228. Reaching The Attic is impossible because of the pipe's unusual nature. Travelers have noted the disturbing sounds of an orchestra emanating from The Attic. Any attempts to talk to Alan about The Attic will be unsuccessful.</span>
|-| Timeout Bath=
{{Blurimage|file=TimeoutBath228.png|hovertext=Timeout Bath|caption=<span style="font-family:Georgia">An image of Timeout Bath.|bg-align=Right|align=Right}}
<span style="font-family:Georgia">'''Timeout Bath''' resembles a standard bathroom, though it contains several chairs and no visible water source. This room appears to be a component of the level’s autonomous environmental system.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">This room is associated with periods of temporal distortion. Individuals report experiencing heightened hunger, anxiety, and auditory intensification of the orchestral composition during extended stays.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Some wanderers who had refused food in The Kitchen later reported that they had reappeared in this room without a clear transition. The duration of stay is inconsistent across documented instances.</span> 

</tabber>
== <span style="color:#D4AF37;"><span style="font-family:Georgia">Entities</span></span> ==
<tabber>
|-| Alan=
{{Blurimage|file=Alan'sPhoto.png|hovertext=Alan's Photo|caption=<span style="font-family:Georgia">An image of '''Alan''' in The Kitchen.</span>|bg-align=Right|align=Right|}}
<span style="font-family:Georgia">'''Alan''', also known as [[Entity 96]], is the only stably observable entity on Level 228.</span>
<span style="font-family:Georgia">Alan manifests primarily in The Kitchen and appears as a plate-shaped form, with food elements forming its facial features. Its "limbs" consist of kitchen utensils that are not physically attached.</span>

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Despite its appearance, Alan's behavior appears consistent under observation periods, though long-term patterns are unclear.</span>

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Alan has only been observed in The Kitchen. Attempts to confirm independent movement have produced inconsistent results.</span> 

<span style="font-family:Georgia">When photographed or recorded through optical devices, Alan does not appear in the resulting image. Instead, a uniform black rectangular occlusion is consistently observed, regardless of angle, lighting, or device type.</span>

<span style="font-family:Georgia">During nighttime, Alan enters a state of stasis until daytime.</span>
|-| Lulubelle=
{{Blurimage|file=LulubelleTheCow228.png|hovertext=Lulubelle's Photo|caption=<span style="font-family:Georgia">An image of '''Lulubelle''' standing in the field.</span>|bg-align=Right|align=Right|}}
<span style="font-family:Georgia">'''Lulubelle''', also known as [[Entity 97]], is a rare and little-studied entity that manifests only within the confines of a house. The entity remains motionless, observing wanderers approaching her.</span>

<span style="font-family:Georgia">Direct visual contact with Lulubelle causes a persistent sensation of noise, paranoia, and visual hallucinations. When approaching Lulubelle, individuals hear an orchestral suite near [[Entity 97]], whose volume increases exponentially as they near. Lulubelle shows no interaction with environmental systems. The process responsible for food manifestation appears independent from Alan.</span>
</tabber>

== <span style="color:#D4AF37;"><span style="font-family:Georgia">Colonies and Outposts</span></span> ==
<span style="font-family:Georgia">Due to the nature of this level, colonies and outposts cannot be established.</span>

== <span style="color:#D4AF37;"><span style="font-family:Georgia">Entrances and Exits</span></span> ==

=== <span style="color:#D4AF37;"><span style="font-family:Georgia">Entrances</span></span> ===

* <span style="font-family:Georgia">Eating food on any level has a low chance of causing one to wake up later in a bed on that level.</span>
* <span style="font-family:Georgia">Unknown entrance from [[Level 227]].</span>

=== <span style="color:#D4AF37;"><span style="font-family:Georgia">Exits</span></span> ===

* <span style="font-family:Georgia">After a long stay on this level, the individual will begin to feel drowsy before falling asleep. After this, the wanderer will awaken on one of these documented levels:</span>
**<span style="font-family: Georgia;">[[Level 10]]</span>
**<span style="font-family: Georgia;">[[Level 365]]</span>
**<span style="font-family: Georgia;">[[Level 730]]</span>
